message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To gather and analyze research data, start by identifying the specific legal issue or question at hand. Use legal research databases such as Westlaw, LexisNexis, or Bloomberg Law to find relevant statutes, case law, and legal articles. Review the applicable statutes and codes to understand the legal framework. Analyze court decisions to see how laws have been interpreted and applied in similar cases. Consult legal articles and treatises for expert commentary and analysis. Organize the gathered information systematically, noting key points and how they relate to your legal issue. Ensure all sources are current and accurately cited.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
